    public interface Package

    Package v1.1.1 The Package is the main structuring unit in a model. It defines a hierarchy that breaks down a Model. Packages can contain Packages, Classifiers, and so on. A Package belongs to its parent Package, represented as a NameSpace in the metamodel, except for the rootPackage, which belongs to a Project.
